You can support your favorite sport at Miami Trace by purchasing a Patron Donor Ad for $10. With your selection of a sport, that sport team receives $5 of your donation. Your yellow copy of the Donor Ad has a value of $4 to use at the concession stand at any MT event during the school year & your support is noted in the fall & winter sports program. It's a win- win for all!

These are available at fair booth, talk to a coach or any booster member.

Thanks for supporting our MT student athletes!

Last evening during the High School wrestling Tri-match we dedicated a set of wrestling scales in memory of Nancy Sheets. These scales help our wrestlers and coaching staff stay on top of weight management with integrated Bluetooth technology and data collection.
Money which was received in memory of Nancy was used to purchase the scales. Since Dan, Bryan, and now David are all wrestlers it was a consensus in discussion with the family this would be the best way to honor Nancy.

Robin Schwartz is with Nikki Riley and 32 others.
April 7, 2016 at 3:13 PM ·

The Miami Trace girls softball team will be having a cancer game against WCH on Friday, April 29th, at 5:00 at Trace.The game is a fundraiser for Ed & Debbie Napier ,who both have been battling a long road of cancer.MT will be wearing black,which represents skin cancer,which Debbie has.WCH will be wearing blue,which represents rectal cancer,for Ed.Their granddaughter/adoptive daughter they've raised, Harmonee, plays for MT.The Napiers are big supporters & Booster members who have done so much for the kids over 20+ yrs.They are going through a rough time right now & we are trying to give back to them,as much as they have gave to our kids.All proceeds from shirt sales will go back to the Napier family.Orders are due by Thurs.,April 14th.Cost are $10 kids-xl adult, sizes 2x $12, & 3x $13.Any questions or to order one,contact me or any Miami Trace or Wch softball player.Please make checks payable to Miami Trace Softball.Thank you!

shared_text:
Miami Trace Softball Team
March 26, 2016 at 6:13 PM ·

Miami Trace Varsity lost second game 18-15
Was rallying last inning but fell short.
Not a bad day scored a total of 29 points on offense. While allowing 18 defensively. Brooke Henry had a home run in first game.
Great turnout at home! Thanks for supporting your Panthers.

JV lost their second game also
Final of game 2 MTJV 12 - Zane Trace 15
JV scored 28 points offensively, while allowing 26 points defensively.

Beautiful day to be at the ball fields.
Varsity will be in action on Tuesday at home at 5:00 pm

JV will be playing at Fairfield Union on Tuesday night around 5:15.
